<style>
  .api-card { transition: all 0.15s; }
  .api-card:hover { border-color: #22c55e; }
  .method-badge { font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }
  pre.code-block { background: #0f172a; color: #e2e8f0; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.7; font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace; }
  .dark pre.code-block { background: #0c1222; }
  .copy-btn { position: absolute; top: 8px; right: 8px; padding: 4px 10px; font-size: 11px; }
</style>

<div class="mb-5">
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Base URL: <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono text-green-600 dark:text-green-400"><%= baseUrl %></code></p>
  <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500 mt-1">All endpoints accept and return JSON. Authentication via <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">x-api-key</code> header is required.</p>
</div>

<div class="space-y-5">

  <!-- Authentication -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z"/></svg>
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Authentication</h3>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">All API requests require a per-device API key sent via the <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-mono">x-api-key</code> header.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">How to get your API key</h4>
    <ol class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 list-decimal list-inside space-y-1 mb-4">
      <li>Go to the <strong>Devices</strong> page in the dashboard</li>
      <li>Click on a device to view its details</li>
      <li>Copy the <strong>API Key</strong> shown for that device</li>
    </ol>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Example Header</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">x-api-key: your-device-api-key-here</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-500/5 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-3">
      <p class="text-xs text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400"><strong>Note:</strong> Each device has its own unique API key. The session ID is automatically resolved from your API key — you don't need to know it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Shorthand Routes Info -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-green-200 dark:border-green-800 p-5">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-green-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/></svg>
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold">Simplified API Routes</h3>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">All endpoints support a <strong>shorthand format</strong> that automatically resolves the device from your API key. No need to include the session ID in the URL:</p>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">// Shorthand (recommended) — device resolved from API key
POST /api/send-message
POST /api/download-media
PUT  /api/webhook
GET  /api/session
POST /api/restart
GET  /api/messages
GET  /api/contacts
POST /api/read
POST /api/presence

// Full format (also supported)
POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/send-message
POST /api/sessions/:sessionId/download-media
...</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 my-2"></div>

  <!-- Send Text Message -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/send-message</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Send a text message to a WhatsApp number.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
  "message": {
    "text": "Hello from WA Gateway!"
  }
}</pre>
    </div>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Response</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "status": "success",
  "messageId": "BAE5A1234567890"
}</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-500/5 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-500/20 rounded-lg p-3">
      <p class="text-xs text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400"><strong>JID Format:</strong> Use <code>phone@s.whatsapp.net</code> for personal chats and <code>groupid@g.us</code> for group chats. Phone number must include country code without <code>+</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Send Image -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/sessions/:sessionId/send-message</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Send an image with optional caption.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
  "message": {
    "image": { "url": "https://example.com/photo.jpg" },
    "caption": "Check this out!"
  }
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Send Document -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/sessions/:sessionId/send-message</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Send a document/file.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
  "message": {
    "document": { "url": "https://example.com/report.pdf" },
    "mimetype": "application/pdf",
    "fileName": "report.pdf"
  }
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Send Video -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/sessions/:sessionId/send-message</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Send a video with optional caption.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
  "message": {
    "video": { "url": "https://example.com/clip.mp4" },
    "caption": "Video message"
  }
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Send Location -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/sessions/:sessionId/send-message</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Send a location pin.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
  "message": {
    "location": {
      "degreesLatitude": -6.2088,
      "degreesLongitude": 106.8456
    }
  }
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Send Buttons -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/sessions/:sessionId/send-message</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Send a message with buttons.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
  "message": {
    "text": "Choose an option:",
    "footer": "Powered by WA Gateway",
    "buttons": [
      { "buttonId": "btn1", "buttonText": { "displayText": "Option 1" } },
      { "buttonId": "btn2", "buttonText": { "displayText": "Option 2" } }
    ],
    "headerType": 1
  }
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 my-2"></div>

  <!-- Webhook Setup -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-amber-100 dark:bg-amber-500/10 text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold">PUT</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/sessions/:sessionId/webhook</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Set a webhook URL for a specific device/session. All incoming messages will be forwarded to this URL via POST.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "url": "https://hook.eu2.make.com/your-webhook-id"
}</pre>
    </div>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Response</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "message": "Webhook updated",
  "sessionId": "device-1",
  "url": "https://hook.eu2.make.com/your-webhook-id"
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Global Webhook -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/settings/webhook</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Set a global webhook that receives messages from <strong>all</strong> devices.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "url": "https://hook.eu2.make.com/your-global-webhook-id"
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Get Global Webhook -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-blue-100 dark:bg-blue-500/10 text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400 font-bold">GET</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/settings/webhook</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Get the current global webhook URL.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Response</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "url": "https://hook.eu2.make.com/your-global-webhook-id"
}</pre>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 my-2"></div>

  <!-- Webhook Payload -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5">
    <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Webhook Payload Format</h3>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">When a message is received, a <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">POST</code> request is sent to your webhook URL. The payload varies by message type:</p>

    <!-- Text Message -->
    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Text Message</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "event": "messages.upsert",
  "sessionId": "device-1",
  "data": {
    "key": {
      "remoteJid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
      "fromMe": false,
      "id": "BAE5A1234567890"
    },
    "pushName": "John Doe",
    "message": {
      "conversation": "Hello, this is a test message"
    },
    "messageTimestamp": 1707868800
  },
  "senderInfo": {
    "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
    "pushName": "John Doe",
    "contactName": "John Doe"
  }
}</pre>
    </div>

    <!-- Image Message -->
    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Image Message</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "event": "messages.upsert",
  "sessionId": "device-1",
  "data": {
    "key": {
      "remoteJid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
      "fromMe": false,
      "id": "3EB0A1B2C3D4E5F6"
    },
    "pushName": "John Doe",
    "message": {
      "imageMessage": {
        "url": "https://mmg.whatsapp.net/...",
        "mimetype": "image/jpeg",
        "caption": "Check this photo",
        "fileSha256": "...",
        "fileLength": 123456,
        "height": 1080,
        "width": 1920,
        "mediaKey": "...",
        "jpegThumbnail": "&lt;base64 thumbnail&gt;"
      }
    },
    "messageTimestamp": 1707868800
  },
  "senderInfo": {
    "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
    "pushName": "John Doe",
    "contactName": "John Doe"
  }
}</pre>
    </div>

    <!-- Document/PDF Message -->
    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Document / PDF Message</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "event": "messages.upsert",
  "sessionId": "device-1",
  "data": {
    "key": {
      "remoteJid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
      "fromMe": false,
      "id": "3EB0F1E2D3C4B5A6"
    },
    "pushName": "John Doe",
    "message": {
      "documentMessage": {
        "url": "https://mmg.whatsapp.net/...",
        "mimetype": "application/pdf",
        "title": "Report.pdf",
        "fileSha256": "...",
        "fileLength": 456789,
        "fileName": "Report.pdf",
        "mediaKey": "...",
        "jpegThumbnail": "&lt;base64 thumbnail&gt;"
      }
    },
    "messageTimestamp": 1707868800
  },
  "senderInfo": {
    "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
    "pushName": "John Doe",
    "contactName": "John Doe"
  }
}</pre>
    </div>

    <!-- Message Status Update -->
    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Message Status Update</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "event": "messages.update",
  "sessionId": "device-1",
  "data": {
    "messageId": "BAE5A1234567890",
    "remoteJid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
    "fromMe": true,
    "statusCode": 4,
    "status": "read",
    "timestamp": 1707868900
  }
}</pre>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-2 mb-2">
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">Status codes: <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">1</code> pending, <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">2</code> server_ack, <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">3</code> delivered, <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">4</code> read, <code class="text-xs bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">5</code> played</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-500/5 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-500/20 rounded-lg p-3">
      <p class="text-xs text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400"><strong>Media Note:</strong> The <code class="text-xs">url</code> inside <code class="text-xs">imageMessage</code> / <code class="text-xs">documentMessage</code> is a temporary WhatsApp CDN URL that expires. To download the actual file, use the <strong>Download Media</strong> endpoint below, passing the <code class="text-xs">data</code> object as the request body.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-2 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-500/5 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-3">
      <p class="text-xs text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400"><strong>Make.com Tip:</strong> In Make.com, create a <strong>Custom Webhook</strong> module as the trigger. Copy the webhook URL and set it via the API or in the Devices page. The incoming data will be automatically parsed.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Download Media -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5 api-card">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="method-badge px-2 py-0.5 rounded bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-500/10 text-green-700 dark:text-green-400 font-bold">POST</span>
      <code class="text-sm font-mono text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">/api/sessions/:sessionId/download-media</code>
    </div>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">Download media (image, video, audio, document) from a received message. Returns the file as base64.</p>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Request Body</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "message": {
    "key": { "remoteJid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net", "id": "MSG_ID" },
    "message": {
      "imageMessage": {
        "url": "https://mmg.whatsapp.net/...",
        "mimetype": "image/jpeg",
        "mediaKey": "..."
      }
    }
  }
}</pre>
    </div>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Response</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">{
  "success": true,
  "mediaType": "image",
  "mimetype": "image/jpeg",
  "filename": "photo.jpg",
  "filesize": 123456,
  "caption": "Check this photo",
  "base64": "/9j/4AAQSkZJRg...",
  "dataUrl": "data:image/jpeg;base64,/9j/4AAQSkZJRg..."
}</pre>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-4 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-500/5 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-500/20 rounded-lg p-3">
      <p class="text-xs text-blue-700 dark:text-blue-400"><strong>Tip:</strong> Pass the entire <code class="text-xs">data</code> object from the webhook payload as the <code class="text-xs">message</code> field. The <code class="text-xs">dataUrl</code> in the response can be used directly in <code class="text-xs">&lt;img&gt;</code> tags.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- cURL Examples -->
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 p-5">
    <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-3">Quick Examples (cURL)</h3>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mb-2">Send Text</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">curl -X POST <%= baseUrl %>/api/send-message \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "x-api-key: your-device-api-key" \
  -d '{
    "jid": "6281234567890@s.whatsapp.net",
    "message": { "text": "Hello from cURL!" }
  }'</pre>
    </div>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Set Webhook</h4>
    <div class="relative">
      <pre class="code-block">curl -X PUT <%= baseUrl %>/api/webhook \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "x-api-key: your-device-api-key" \
  -d '{ "url": "https://hook.eu2.make.com/your-id" }'</pre>
    </div>

    <h4 class="text-xs font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase mt-4 mb-2">Check Session Status</h4>
    <div class="relative">
